#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4492
msgid "Catches password-guessing attacks. We count wrong passwords per IP. Once an IP exceeds the limit within the window, it is treated as a threat. A second layer also fires if one IP probes many different usernames in a short window (password-spray / credential-stuffing)."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4498
msgid "Watch failed logins"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4504
msgid "How many wrong passwords?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4506
msgid "Trigger after this many failed attempts from one IP. 5 is a good starting point."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4509
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4523
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4551
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4580
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4615
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4642
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4678
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4705
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:5161
msgid "Within how many minutes?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4511
msgid "Counters reset after this window. Shorter = stricter, but more sensitive to legitimate users mistyping their password."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4515
msgid "Password-spray detection"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4516
msgid "Triggers when one IP tries many different usernames quickly — a stronger signal than the per-IP attempt count above."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4519
msgid "How many distinct usernames?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4532
#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:7109
msgid "Comment spam"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4534
msgid "When the same IP submits comments that WordPress flags as spam in rapid succession, treat that IP as a threat."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4540
msgid "Watch comment spam"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4546
msgid "How many spam comments?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4548
msgid "Counts comments WordPress already marked as spam. 3 catches most bots."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4553
msgid "Counter window. Real spammers post quickly — 60 minutes is generous."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4561
msgid "XML-RPC abuse"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4563
msgid "XML-RPC is an older WordPress remote-control interface that bots often hammer to brute-force passwords. Most modern sites do not actively use it."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4569
msgid "Watch XML-RPC requests"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4575
msgid "How many requests?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4577
msgid "Trigger after this many XML-RPC calls from one IP."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4582
msgid "Counter window for XML-RPC requests."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4590
msgid "Application password abuse"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4592
msgid "Application passwords authenticate over REST and XML-RPC and skip the normal login 2FA prompt. We rate-limit failed app-password sign-ins and can optionally block new app passwords for 2FA-enforced roles until enrolment is finished."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4598
msgid "Watch application-password authentications"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4605
msgid "Block app-password creation until 2FA enrolment is finished (for enforced roles)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4611
msgid "How many failed auths?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4624
msgid "REST API abuse"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4626
msgid "Per-IP rate limit on /wp-json/* requests. Catches scrapers and vulnerability scanners that hammer the REST surface. Sensitive routes (/wp/v2/users, /wp/v2/comments) use a tighter threshold by default."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4632
msgid "Watch REST API requests"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4638
msgid "Global requests threshold"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4646
msgid "Sensitive-route threshold"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4648
msgid "Tighter limit for /wp/v2/users and /wp/v2/comments."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4651
msgid "Sensitive timeframe (min)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4660
msgid "User enumeration defence"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4662
msgid "Closes the four classic username-leak vectors: ?author= probes, /wp-json/wp/v2/users, oEmbed author leaks, and the verbose \"user does not exist\" login error. Repeated probes from one IP also trip the auto-block."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4668
msgid "Block username discovery and unify login errors"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4674
msgid "How many probes?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4687
msgid "404 / Scanner detection"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4689
msgid "Catches vulnerability scanners. A single hit on a known-bad path (.env, wp-config.php.bak, /.git/config, /phpmyadmin, …) triggers immediately; bursts of regular 404s also count."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4695
msgid "Watch suspicious 404s and known scanner paths"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4701
msgid "404 burst threshold"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4714
msgid "Skip burst triggers for verified search engines and AI crawlers (User-Agent based)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4716
msgid "Googlebot, Bingbot, DuckDuckBot, GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot, Amazonbot and similar crawlers are exempt from the 404 burst trigger and the REST burst trigger. Pattern-based detection (.env, wp-config.php.bak, /phpmyadmin/, …) stays active for all visitors, including spoofed bot User-Agents."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4723
msgid "WooCommerce login"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4725
msgid "Hooks into WooCommerce-specific login failures (my-account form, checkout AJAX login). Uses the same threshold as Failed login attempts."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4731
msgid "Watch WooCommerce login attempts"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4739
msgid "Geographic anomaly"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4741
msgid "Watches successful logins. When a user signs in from a country or network (ASN) not seen in the recent look-back window, the event is logged and trusted-device cookies can be revoked to force a fresh 2FA challenge. Location data reuses the cached community lookup, so no extra request is made."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4747
msgid "Watch logins from new countries / networks"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4754
msgid "Revoke trusted-device cookies on geo anomaly (forces 2FA on next login)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4761
msgid "Also share anomalies with the community network (off by default — informational)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4765
msgid "Look-back window (days)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4767
msgid "How long a country/ASN stays \"known\" for a user."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4774
msgid "Password strength policy"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4776
msgid "Enforces a minimum length, character-class diversity and an optional public-breach check (HaveIBeenPwned k-anonymity — only the first 5 SHA-1 hex characters of the password leave the server). Applies to users in the 2FA-enforced roles by default."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4782
msgid "Enforce password policy"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4789
msgid "Reject passwords that appear in public breaches (HaveIBeenPwned, k-anonymity protocol)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4796
msgid "Apply to all users (default: only 2FA-enforced roles)"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4802
msgid "Minimum length"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-admin-settings.php:4806
